text: Josef Panáček (8 September 1937 – 5 April 2022) was a Czechoslovak sport shooter. He won a gold medal in skeet shooting at the 1976 Summer Olympics in Montreal."1976 Summer Olympics - Montreal, Canada - Shooting" databaseOlympics.com (Retrieved on 27 September 2008) He was born in Staré Město, Czechoslovakia.
